text.section:
An other tobacco products manufacturer may:
sell other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid to:
a licensed other tobacco products wholesaler located in Maryland;
a licensed other tobacco products wholesaler located outside Maryland if the other tobacco products may be sold lawfully in Maryland; or
a licensed tobacconist;
sell premium cigars or pipe tobacco on which the tobacco tax has not been paid to a licensed other tobacco products retailer;
except as otherwise prohibited or restricted under local law, this article, or the Criminal Law Article, distribute sample other tobacco products to consumers located in Maryland;
store other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid in a licensed other tobacco products storage warehouse for subsequent shipment to licensed other tobacco products wholesalers, federal reservations, or persons out of state; and
on approval of the Comptroller, act as an agent of a Maryland other tobacco products wholesaler for distribution of other tobacco products.

An other tobacco products wholesaler license authorizes the licensee to:
act as an other tobacco products wholesaler;
buy other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid directly from an other tobacco products manufacturer;
hold other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid;
transport other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid in the State;
sell other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid to another licensed other tobacco products wholesaler if the Comptroller specifically authorizes; and
store other tobacco products on which the tobacco tax has not been paid at a licensed other tobacco products storage warehouse.
